Carlo Archinto of Milan (1669-1732); Adolph Sutro (1830-1898), mayor of San Francisco. A letter from George Moss (librarian of Sutro) addressed to Mrs. Morbio (presumably Mrs. Albert Morbio, Sutro's daughter), 23 May 1890, accompanies the manuscript.
Carthusians of Buxheim; Hugo, Graf von Waldbott-Bassenhim (his sale, Munich, 20 September 1883, lot 2672); Adolph Sutro (1830-1898), mayor of San Francisco.

Inside front cover: Ex bibliotheca Com. Eq. Fabricii Orsini Rilli di Poppi. N. 263 in a Sotheby sale, ca. 1890 (according to De Ricci); Adolph Sutro (1830-1898), mayor of San Francisco.
